2 Garlic
1 packet Rosemary
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet Parsley
1 Baby Broccoli
1 Red Onion
2 packet Potato
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
300 g Premium Fillet Steak
1 Fresh Chilli
1 drizzle olive oil
g butter

• See ‘Top Roast Tips!’ (below left).
• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Season premium fillet steak with salt and pepper.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. When oil is hot, cook fillet until browned, 1 minute each side.
• Transfer to a lined oven tray and roast for 10-15 minutes (2 person portion) or 15-20 minutes (4 person portion), or until cooked to your liking.
TIP: Cook time will vary depending on the thickness of the fillet. The thinner the steak, the less time it needs to cook!

• While the fillet is browning, cut potato into bite-sized chunks.
• Pick and finely chop rosemary.
• Place potato on a second lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, sprinkle over rosemary and season with salt. Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 25-30 minutes.
TIP: Run your fingers down the rosemary stalk to remove the leaves easily.

• While the potatoes are roasting, pick parsley.
• Finely chop parsley and garlic.
• Thinly slice onion (see ingredients).
• Halve any thicker stalks of baby broccoli (see ingredients) lengthways.
• Roughly chop baby leaves.
• Thinly slice fresh chilli (if using).

• In a medium bowl, combine the butter, parsley and half the garlic.
• Season with pepper, then mash together with a fork. Set aside.
• When the fillet has finished cooking, transfer to a plate, then top with garlic-herb butter.
• Cover loosely with foil and set aside to rest.
TIP: Soften the butter mixture for 10 seconds in the
microwave if you're finding it hard to combine!

• While the fillet is resting, return the frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook onion and baby broccoli, tossing, until tender, 5-6 minutes.
• Add baby leaves, chilli and remaining garlic and cook, stirring until leaves have wilted, 1-2 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then stir through grated Parmesan cheese.

• Slice steak.
• Divide herby potatoes, steak and Parmesan veggies between plates.
• Spoon any beef resting juices and remaining garlic butter over beef to serve. Enjoy!